            <h2>Chinese Family Lawyer with Peel Region Court Experience</h2>
            <p>Brampton is Peel Region's core city — one of Canada's fastest-growing urban areas, with a rapidly expanding Chinese-Canadian community. Miao He provides full Mandarin family law services to Brampton clients and is familiar with Peel Region court practices and local family law procedure.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h2>Divorce &amp; Property Division in Brampton</h2>
            <p>Brampton families commonly own townhouses and semi-detached homes. At the time of divorce, the increase in property value during the marriage must be shared through Equalization of Net Family Property. Miao He helps clients accurately establish the <strong>valuation date</strong> — the date of separation — and the value of pre-marital assets to be excluded, ensuring a fair and legally correct division.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h2>Child Custody Under Ontario's Updated Law</h2>
            <p>Ontario updated the Children, Youth and Family Services Act in 2023. The term "custody" is now replaced by <strong>Decision-Making Responsibility</strong> (who makes major decisions about the child's life) and <strong>Parenting Time</strong> (when the child is with each parent). Miao He drafts detailed Parenting Plans that cover education, medical decisions, religious observance, holidays, and vacation schedules — reducing future disputes.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h2>Marriage Contract Requirements in Ontario</h2>
            <p>A Marriage Contract (Prenuptial Agreement) in Ontario must be reviewed by independent legal counsel for each party to be enforceable. Miao He provides full Chinese-language drafting and ensures the agreement meets Ontario court scrutiny standards — a poorly drafted contract can be set aside by a court as unconscionable.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h2>Domestic Violence &amp; Emergency Orders</h2>
            <p>If you are facing domestic violence or need to urgently protect yourself and your children, Miao He can assist in obtaining an <strong>Emergency Restraining Order</strong> and <strong>Exclusive Possession of the Matrimonial Home</strong> — removing an abusive spouse from the shared home while legal proceedings continue.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Question</h2>
            <p class="faq-q">Brampton family law cases — which court?</p>
            <p>Brampton cases are heard at the Ontario Court of Justice or Superior Court of Justice in Peel Region, depending on the type of proceeding. Miao He is familiar with both courts and will advise on the right venue for your matter.</p>
          </div>
